A Function That Exports a Table of Dyadic Invariance Model Comparison Indices

dyMIOutput.Rd

This function takes the model from fitted dyCFA() scripts and exports a table of expected output.

dyMIOutput(config, load, int, robust = F)

Arguments

config

fitted dyadic configural invariance model lavaan object
load

fitted dyadic loading invariance model lavaan object
int

fitted dyadic intercept invariance model lavaan object
robust

logical for whether a robust estimator has been used (default is F)

Value

Prints word files for the table outputed to the users working directory

See also

dyadCFA which this function relies on

Examples

dvn <- dyadVarNames(dat, xvar="X",  sep = ".",
distinguish1 = "1", distinguish2 = "2")

con.config.script = dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "Conflict",  model = "configural")
#> Error in dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "Conflict", model = "configural"): could not find function "dyadCFA"
con.loading.script = dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "Conflict",  model = "loading")
#> Error in dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "Conflict", model = "loading"): could not find function "dyadCFA"
con.intercept.script = dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "Conflict",  model = "intercept")
#> Error in dyadCFA(dvn, lvname = "Conflict", model = "intercept"): could not find function "dyadCFA"

con.fit.config <- lavaan::cfa(con.config.script, data = dat, std.lv = FALSE, auto.fix.first= FALSE, meanstructure = TRUE)
#> Error in lavaan::lavaan(model = con.config.script, data = dat, std.lv = FALSE,     auto.fix.first = TRUE, meanstructure = TRUE, model.type = "cfa",     int.ov.free = TRUE, int.lv.free = FALSE, auto.fix.single = TRUE,     auto.var = TRUE, auto.cov.lv.x = TRUE, auto.cov.y = TRUE,     auto.th = TRUE, auto.delta = TRUE, auto.efa = TRUE): object 'con.config.script' not found
con.fit.loading <- lavaan::cfa(con.loading.script, data = dat, std.lv = FALSE, auto.fix.first= FALSE, meanstructure = TRUE)
#> Error in lavaan::lavaan(model = con.loading.script, data = dat, std.lv = FALSE,     auto.fix.first = TRUE, meanstructure = TRUE, model.type = "cfa",     int.ov.free = TRUE, int.lv.free = FALSE, auto.fix.single = TRUE,     auto.var = TRUE, auto.cov.lv.x = TRUE, auto.cov.y = TRUE,     auto.th = TRUE, auto.delta = TRUE, auto.efa = TRUE): object 'con.loading.script' not found
con.fit.intercept <- lavaan::cfa(con.intercept.script, data = dat, std.lv = FALSE, auto.fix.first= FALSE, meanstructure = TRUE)
#> Error in lavaan::lavaan(model = con.intercept.script, data = dat, std.lv = FALSE,     auto.fix.first = TRUE, meanstructure = TRUE, model.type = "cfa",     int.ov.free = TRUE, int.lv.free = FALSE, auto.fix.single = TRUE,     auto.var = TRUE, auto.cov.lv.x = TRUE, auto.cov.y = TRUE,     auto.th = TRUE, auto.delta = TRUE, auto.efa = TRUE): object 'con.intercept.script' not found
